</o:p></span></p>
<div>
<div style=3D"border:none;border-top:solid #E1E1E1 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in =
0in 0in">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><b><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot=
;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ligatures:none">From:</span></b><span style=
=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;mso-ligatur=
es:none"> Grant Metson &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Gran=
t.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;
<br>
<b>Sent:</b> Monday, 13 April 2026 3:15 PM<br>
<b>To:</b> Richard Hargreaves &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Richard.Hargreaves@wynn=
williams.co.nz">Richard.Hargreaves@wynnwilliams.co.nz</a>&gt;; Rachael Keen=
an &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Rachael.Keenan@tower.co.nz">Rachael.Keenan@tower.c=
o.nz</a>&gt;; Abigail Collin &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Abigail.Collin@wynnwilli=
ams.co.nz">Abigail.Collin@wynnwilliams.co.nz</a>&gt;<br>
<b>Cc:</b> Jessica Laughland &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Jessica.Laughland@tower.=
co.nz">Jessica.Laughland@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;; Bryan Strong &lt;<a href=3D"m=
ailto:Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz">Bryan.Strong@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;; Flynn Mil=
ler &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Flynn.Miller@wynnwilliams.co.nz">Flynn.Miller@wyn=
nwilliams.co.nz</a>&gt;;
 Lance O'Riley &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Lance.ORiley@tower.co.nz">Lance.ORiley=
@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;; Claims &lt;<a href=3D"mailto:Claims@tower.co.nz">Clai=
ms@tower.co.nz</a>&gt;<br>
<b>Subject:</b> RE: CLAIM C90306048 -Fire at 23 Mays Street Devonport 2026-=
001966 [WYNNW-ACTIVE.FID3167762]<o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Richard, and =
All,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Thanks for the repl=
y sent to Tower Insurance below, received on April 9.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have spoken with =
my colleagues, and we agree that Tower Insurance should provide further det=
ailed response to each of the concerns presented within the Prendos Report.=
 As such instructions have been issued
 as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 =
lfo3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have instructed ASURNZ to provide =
detailed response with respect to the application of Schedule 1, and provid=
e specific reference to the relevant clauses
 within the Building Act 2004; and any other relevant legislation which wil=
l assist with determination on this issue. I will be able to provide that r=
esponse to you by 4pm on Tuesday April 21.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=
=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><sp=
an style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have instructed ASURNZ to appoint a CPEng t=
o undertake an assessment of the unreinforced masonry walls to the perimete=
r of the basement level of the
 dwelling to ascertain if they have been materially affected by the loss-ev=
ent [fire].<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"m=
argin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I =
have instructed ASURNZ to appoint a CPEng to undertake an assessment of the=
 existing wall bracing elements which are referred to in the Prendos report.
<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:=
0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have instru=
cted ASURNZ to provide drawings of construction details, specification refe=
rences, and other documents which will assist with authenticating
 the aspects of the repairs which are currently within the proposed scope o=
f works. This should provide further clarity and detail for all parties to =
review.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margi=
n-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have=
 instructed ASURNZ to include the replacement of existing thermal insulatio=
n to the external basement walls into the proposed scope of work.<o:p></o:p=
></span></li></ol>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">To complete all the=
 above we request permission to access the property at
<u>9am on Thursday April 16</u> to allow for assessments and observations t=
o be completed. Noting that item #4 may take a while longer to provide as t=
he drawings will be produced from additional notes &amp; observations taken=
 on the proposed site visit. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Persons who would b=
e present at this site review are as follows:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<ul style=3D"margin-top:0in" type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 =
lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant Metson =E2=80=93 Regional Mana=
ger, Structural Assessing, Tower Insurance.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=
=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo6"><sp=
an style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Warwick Banks =E2=80=93 CPEng. KCL Engineerin=
g.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-lef=
t:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo6"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Stephen Wal=
ker =E2=80=93 Principal Consultant, ASURNZ.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please relay this r=
equest to Raffaella Del Prete, in order that we receive her permission to v=
isit the property to complete the above, at the date and time prescribed.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Please confirm at y=
our earliest ability, so I can reconfirm this with all parties.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Best Regards,<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant.<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
